========================
Python-specific Ignored Files
========================
Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
pycache/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

C extensions
*.so
*.os
*.dll
*.pyd

Distribution / Packaging
These folders contain the build artifacts, including the final .msi, .exe, etc.
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.eggs/

Environments
.venv/
venv/
env/
/bin/
/include/
/lib/
/lib64/

Test / Coverage
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.nox/

Third-party dependencies
If using pip freeze, requirements.txt should be committed, but the packages themselves shouldn't
If you check-in requirements.txt, you can uncomment the next line
pip-wheel-cache/
========================
Installer/MSI Specific Ignored Files
========================
Output files from installer creation tools (like WiX, setuptools, cx_Freeze, PyInstaller)
*.msi
*.exe
*.pkg
*.dmg
*.spec # PyInstaller spec files, often generated in the root or build/

Temporary files created during the build process
Specific to certain setups, but often covered by 'build/'
_MEI*/

